
<h3>
    What is a diode?
</h3>

<ul>
    <li>
        A diode is a device that only allows current to flow in a single direction.
    </li>
    <li>
        If the diode is connected one way, it provides almost no resistance.
        if it is reversed, it provides a very high resistance.
    </li>
    <li>
        The most well known type of diode is a <strong>light emitting diode (LED)</strong>,
        which makes a small light of a specific wavelength (color) if current moves through it.
    </li>
</ul>

